  "texts": [
    "Agents can directly alter environment states by actions, such as moving their positions, collecting items, and constructing buildings.",
    "For instance, in GITM [16] and Voyager [38], the environments are changed by the actions of the agents in their task completion process.",
    "For example, if the agent mines three woods, then they may disappear in the environments.",
    "(2) Altering internal states.",
    "Actions taken by the agent can also change the agent itself, including updating memories, forming new plans, acquiring novel knowledge, and more."
  ],
